Cocoa Prices in N.Y. Head for Longest Slump Since 1961

-- B y   P a t r i c k   M c K i e r n a n
-- 
2011-12-08T22:20:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/cocoa-prices-in-n-y-head-for-longest-slump-since-1961-correct-.html
(Corrects year in headline and first paragraph.)  Cocoa for March delivery fell $17, or
0.8 percent, to $2,125 a metric ton at 8:54 a.m. on ICE Futures
U.S. in  New York . The price headed for the 11th straight
decline, the longest slump since at least 1961.  Earlier, the commodity touched $2,097, the lowest for a
most-active contract since November 2008.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Patrick McKiernan at 
 pmckiernan@bloomberg.net  